From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ahmed ARIF <arif.ing@outlook.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] libgcc: add mingw/t-seh-eh make fragment

The aarch64-*-mingw* support patches enable SEH unwinding by referencing
`mingw/t-seh-eh` in `libgcc/config.host`, but GCC does not ship that
fragment. Provide it so the build uses SEH unwinding (unwind-seh.c)
instead of DW2 unwinding on Windows targets.
---
 libgcc/config/mingw/t-seh-eh | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 libgcc/config/mingw/t-seh-eh

diff --git a/libgcc/config/mingw/t-seh-eh b/libgcc/config/mingw/t-seh-eh
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..c3655b8de
--- /dev/null
+++ b/libgcc/config/mingw/t-seh-eh
@@ -0,0 +1,6 @@
+
+# We are using SEH EH.
+EH_MODEL = seh
+
+# Use SEH exception handling.
+LIB2ADDEH = $(srcdir)/unwind-seh.c $(srcdir)/unwind-sjlj.c $(srcdir)/unwind-c.c
